

## TASK-006 Report: Implement Stability Indicators

### Status: ✓ Completed

### Summary
Implemented delete-one, replace-one, add-one, and LOO stability indicators with comprehensive tests. All 149 tests pass (30 new stability tests + 119 existing tests).

### Implementation Details

**Core Functions (in `src/knn_stability/stability.py`):**

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `binary_loss` | Binary 0-1 loss helper |
| `delete_one_sample` | Creates S⁻ⁱ by deleting i-th occurrence |
| `replace_one_sample` | Creates S^{i←z} by replacing with (x', y') |
| `add_one_sample` | Creates S⊕z by appending at end |
| `pointwise_delete_one_stability` | Δ_del(S, i, x, y) with k' = min(k, n-1) |
| `pointwise_replace_one_stability` | Δ_rep(S, i, z, x, y) |
| `pointwise_add_one_stability` | Δ_add(S, z, x, y) |
| `pointwise_loo_stability` | Δ_loo(S, i) evaluates at (xᵢ, yᵢ) |

**Uniform Stability Helpers:**
- `uniform_delete_one_stability`: O(n·|X|·2) complexity
- `uniform_replace_one_stability`: O(|X|²) per index
- `uniform_add_one_stability`: O(|X|) for fixed z
- `uniform_loo_stability`: O(n) complexity

### Key Distinctions

| Perturbation | Evaluation Point | Sample Size |
|--------------|-----------------|-------------|
| Delete-one | Arbitrary (x, y) | Decreases |
| Replace-one | Arbitrary (x, y) | Unchanged |
| Add-one | Arbitrary (x, y) | Increases |
| LOO | Fixed (xᵢ, yᵢ) | Decreases |

### Computed Limitations Documented
- Uniform stability requires exhaustive enumeration
- Replace-one with z ∈ X×{0,1} has complexity O(n·|X|)
- Tractable only for small metric spaces

